job_description:
You Lead the Way. We’ve Got Your Back.

At American Express, we know that with the right backing, people and businesses have the power to progress in incredible ways. Whether we’re supporting our customers’ financial confidence to move ahead, taking commerce to new heights, or encouraging people to explore the world, our colleagues are constantly redefining what’s possible — and we’re proud to back each other every step of the way.

When you join Team Amex, you become part of a diverse community of over 60,000 colleagues, all with a common goal to deliver an exceptional customer experience every day. Here, you’ll learn and grow as we champion your meaningful career journey with programs, benefits, and flexibility to back you personally and professionally. Every colleague shares in the company’s success.

Together, we’ll win as a team, striving to uphold our company values and powerful backing promise to our customers, communities, and each other every day. And we’ll do it with integrity and in an environment where everyone is seen, heard and feels like they truly belong.

Join #TeamAmex and let’s lead the way together.

As part of our diverse tech team, you can architect, code and ship software that makes us an essential part of our customers’ digital lives. Here, you can work alongside talented engineers in an open, supportive, inclusive environment where your voice is valued, and you make your own decisions on what tech to use to solve challenging problems. American Express offers a range of opportunities to work with the latest technologies and encourages you to back the broader engineering community through open source. And because we understand the importance of keeping your skills fresh and relevant, we give you dedicated time to invest in your professional development. Find your place in technology of #TeamAmex.

Focus:

Contributes to crafting, developing, trouble shooting, debugging, evaluating, modifying, deploying and documenting all data components (data architecture, logical and physical data models, database objects and database administration) that meet the needs of customer-facing applications, business applications, and/or internal end user applications.

Organizational Context:

Entry-level position. Member of a data management and database development team reporting to a Senior Data Engineer, Engineering Director or Director of Technical Delivery.

How will you make an impact in this role?
• Reviews data requirements / data stories and corresponding data sources and data architecture
• Documents data requirements / data stories and maintains data models to ensure flawless integration into existing data architectures
• Supports management of data assets as per the enterprise standards, guidelines and policies
• Reviews and understands the processing requirements inclusive of data and transaction volumes, scalability, security and performance requirements
• Assists in building and improving the database design and infrastructure required to support the Business portfolio
• Assists in performing database design review and supports database testing
• Provides production environment support for database systems and processes
• Communicates and works closely with business and product teams to support changes and implementation
• Function as an active member if an agile team through consistent development practices (tools, components, and documentation)
• Finds opportunities to adopt innovative technologies
• Takes part in reviews of own work or with colleagues
• Work on prioritized/assigned features for ongoing sprints

Range of Impact/Influence:
• Accountable for team completing work you’re leading and work you are doing as agreed upon
• Accountable to team for delivery of quality work

Do you see data or a better way to improve business and lives? Today, there’s a business advantage hiding in plain sight, and you’ll find it in data. Our Data Engineers know how to use the latest technology to design, evaluate, debug and manage the data that leads to better decisions, a stronger company, and higher customer satisfaction. So if you’re not intimidated by the data explosion, engineer your career here. More than the data on what you’ll be doing. There’s no end to the data that’s created every day and the opportunities you find here. But these are just some of your responsibilities: - Document data requirements/data stories and maintain data models - Support the management of data assets according to enterprise standards, guidelines and policies - Help build and enhance the database design that supports our business portfolio - Work collaboratively with business and product teams - Identify opportunities to adopt innovative technologies

Qualifications

Education & Experience:

Up to 2 years of software development experience in a professional environment and/or comparable experience such as:
• Understanding of Agile or other rapid application development methods
• Exposure to design and development across one or more database management systems (e.g. IMS, DB2 zOS, Oracle, MS SQL Server, PostgreSQL, Netezza (PDA/DB2AA)) as appropriate
• Exposure to methods relating to application and database design, development and automated testing
• Understanding of Big data / NOSQL design and development with variety of data stores (document, column family, graph, etc.)
• Good understanding and Technical knowledge of DBMS products and ecosystem – e.g.
• storage formats, access algorithms, data management processes, administration, data maintenance, replication, high availability, encryption, etc.”
• General knowledge of distributed (multi-tiered) systems, algorithms, and relational & non-relational databases
• Bachelor’s Degree in computer science, computer science engineering, or related field required; advanced degree preferred

High Performance Behaviors:
• Recognizes opportunities to adopt innovative technologies to enable business capabilities
• Able to challenge the status quo and drive innovation by generating creative ideas and solutions
• Keeps up-to-date on current research and technology in the industry
• Understands technical aspects of the job and uses appropriate technology for the situation at hand
• Tries innovative approaches when problem solving, seeking ideas, or suggestions from others as appropriate
• Carries out systematic and rational analysis to identify the root cause of problems
• Recognizes the importance of collaboration to achieve objectives
• Is clear when explaining ideas and concepts to others, communication is structured and easy to understand
• Leads multiple tasks optimally - progresses work in parallel
• Adapts to change quickly and easily
• Handles problems and acts on own initiative without being prompted
• Knows when to raise decisions and when to make on-the-spot decisions

Knowledge/Skills:
• Able to understand and use data structures and associated components
• Basic understanding of Metadata Management and Database Management
• Able to understand and document business data requirements in complete, accurate, extensible and flexible logical data models using data modeling tools – ErStudio, ErWin
• Creates basic data models using the relevant tools and frameworks
• Basic understanding of XML and schema development/reuse, database concepts, database designs, Open Source, big data technology and NoSQL will be an added advantage
• Application of industry recognized methods, processes and standards
• Has understanding of the core tools used in the planning, analyzing, designing, building, testing, configuring and maintaining of assigned application(s)
• Able to participate in assigned team’s software delivery methodology (Agile, Scrum, Agile XP, Test-Driven Development, Waterfall, etc.) in support of data management and database development
• Familiar with infrastructure technologies and components like servers, jvms, databases, and networking concepts

Technology Skills You'll Use Every Day:
• Adaptive Communication
• Agile Practices
• Industry and Company Knowledge
• Organizational Change
• Technical Acuity
• Technology Industry Trends

Game Changers:
• Adaptability
• Collaboration & Partnership
• Continuous Improvement
• Courage
• Curiosity
• Resourcefulness
• Servant Leadership
• Tenacity

Technical
• Database Design

• Performance and Tuning
• System/Platform Domain Knowledge

Functional
• Data Analysis
• Data Management

Leadership

Business

Data Engineer

Work Location: Remote

Duration: 1 Year

Job Description

The data engineer will be responsible for collecting, managing, and converting raw data into information that can be interpreted by data scientists and business analysts. Data accessibility and interoperability will be their ultimate goal, which is to enable organizations to utilize data for performance evaluation and optimization.

Skills:
• Programming Skills: You should have a strong foundation in programming languages like Python, RUST, Java, and Scala.
• Database Skills: You should be proficient in SQL and know about NoSQL databases such as Cassandra, MongoDB, and HBase.
• Data Warehousing: Understanding the concepts of data warehousing, including ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes and data modeling is essential.
• Data Integration: You should be able to integrate data from various sources, such as web services, APIs, and file systems.
• Big Data: Knowledge of distributed computing technologies like Hive, Hadoop, and Spark, is becoming increasingly important for data engineers.
• Cloud Computing: Familiarity with cloud-based storage and computing platforms such as Azure, AWS, and GCP is crucial.
• Data Pipelines: Understanding how to build data pipelines using tools like Apache NiFi, Apache Kafka, and Apache Airflow is critical.
• Version Control: Proficiency in version control systems such as Git and understanding the concepts of branching, merging, and tagging is essential.
• Data Visualization: You should have a good understanding of data visualization tools such as QlikView, Tableau, and Power BI.

Who we are:

Raft (https://goraft.tech) is a customer-obsessed non-traditional small business with purposeful focus on Distributed Data Systems, Platforms at Scale, and Complex Application Development, with headquarters in Reston, VA. Our range of clients include innovative federal and public agencies leveraging design thinking, cutting edge tech stack, and cloud native ecosystem. We build digital solutions that impact the lives of millions of Americans.

Our team is rapidly growing and looking for an experienced Staff Data Engineer to support our customer and join our passionate team of high-impact problem solvers. We enjoy the challenges of human-centered design, security, and scale to create better outcomes for our federal agency partners. We are a remote-first and work completely in the open source.

About the role:

Senior Data Engineers on our Distributed Systems team are focused on building data platforms that make it easy for different types of user personas to access data from a central control plane. This includes building backend services, connecting OSS projects in a repeatable and performant way, and extending feature sets. Experience involving data engineering and all things data. Utilizing new tools like DuckDB, Apache Pinot, Apache Superset, and others while also being a subject matter expert on Spark, including but not limited to Delta Lake, Databricks, GraphX, etc. As the Senior Data Engineer you will be working closely with Technical SMEs on the government side to build the next generation of data platform for mission-critical SOCOM needs.

Required Qualifications:
• Subject Matter Expert on Spark. Should have multiple years of experience in Spark
• Must have used Databricks products as well as know the comparable Open Source alternatives to Databricks
• Must have educational background in CS/EE/Math etc.
• Must keep up to date with trends in the Data Engineering, Data Streaming, and Data Search areas within the community
• If you could grab a coffee with any special person, your answer is Martin Kleppmann
• You love understanding broad requirements, putting them into smaller consumable chunks, and proving that they are achievable by building POCs

Highly preferred:
• Experience building Apache Pinot POCs
• Knowing the operational pros and cons in Custom Off The Shelf (COTS) products and their Open Source Software (OSS) alternatives

Clearance Requirements:
• Ability to obtain and maintain a SECRET clearance or higher

Position Type and Location:
• Remote (Tampa, FL Preferred)

• And More!

Our Vision Statement:

We bridge the gap between humans and data through radical transparency and our obsession with the mission.

Our Customer Obsession:

We will approach every deliverable like it's a product. We will adopt a customer-obsessed mentality. As we grow, and our footprint becomes larger, teams and employees will treat each other not only as teammates but customers. We must live the customer-obsessed mindset, always. This will help us scale and it will translate to the interactions that our Rafters have with their clients and other product teams that they integrate with. Our culture will enable our success and set us apart from other companies.

How do we get there?

Public-sector modernization is critical for us to live in a better world. We, at Raft, want to innovate and solve complex problems. And, if we are successful, our generation and the ones that follow us will live in a delightful, efficient, and accessible world where out-of-box thinking, and collaboration is a norm.

Raft’s core philosophy is Ubuntu: I Am, Because We are. We support our “nadi” by elevating the other Rafters. We work as a hyper collaborative team where each team member brings a unique perspective, adding value that did not exist before. People make Raft special. We celebrate each other and our cognitive and cultural diversity. We are devoted to our practice of innovation and collaboration.

ABOUT THE JOB:
Hopper is looking for an experienced Senior Data Engineer to join our Disruption Protection team. As a Senior Data Engineer, you will work on developing and maintaining data pipelines and infrastructure that enable our team to make data-driven decisions. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams, including Product, Engineering, and Data Science, to identify, collect, and analyze large volumes of data. You will leverage your expertise in building scalable and reliable data systems to help us innovate the future of travel protection technology.
RESPONSIBILITIES:

• Design, develop, and maintain scalable and reliable data pipelines and infrastructure.
• Work with cross-functional teams to identify and collect data from various sources, and analyze and interpret the data to derive insights that drive business decisions.
• Develop and deploy data quality checks and monitoring to ensure data integrity.
• Design and implement efficient and automated data processing workflows.

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS:

• 5+ years of experience in data engineering, designing and building scalable and reliable data pipelines and infrastructure.
• Proficiency in one or more programming languages such as Python, Java, or Scala.
• Experience with data warehousing, ETL, and data processing frameworks like Hadoop, Spark, or Flink.
• Strong SQL skills and familiarity with data analysis tools such as Amplitude, Data Studio, Tableau, or similar.
• Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
• Experience with cloud-based data platforms like AWS or GCP.
• Familiarity with data streaming frameworks like Kafka or Kinesis.
• Experience with workflow management tools like Airflow or Luigi.

As its first Hopper Cloud partnership,

You'll also provide thought leadership and insights on emerging data management solutions.
Meaningful work is fueled by meaningful performance and career development conversations with your manager. Here's some of what you may be asked to perform:

Join SADA as a Senior Data Engineer, Corporate!

Your Mission

As a Senior Data Engineer, Corporate at SADA, you will have the opportunity to work with big data and emerging Google Cloud technologies to drive corporate services. You will have an opportunity to design, develop, and maintain the best Enterprise Data Warehouse solution to fit our corporate needs. You will be interacting with all of our business units and Google Cloud subject matter experts.

From transforming business requirements, solution architecture, data modeling, architecting, ETL, metadata, and business continuity, you will have the opportunity to work collaboratively with architects and other engineers to recommend, prototype, build, and debug data infrastructures on Google Cloud Platform (GCP). You will have an opportunity to work on real-world data problems facing our customers today. Engagements vary from being purely consultative to requiring heavy hands-on work and covering a diverse array of domain areas, such as data migrations, data archival and disaster recovery, and big data analytics solutions requiring batch or streaming data pipelines, data lakes, and data warehouses.

You will be expected to run point on whole projects, end-to-end, and to mentor less experienced Data Engineers. You will be recognized as an expert within the team and will build a reputation with Google and our customers. Who We Are:

SmithRx is a rapidly growing, venture-backed Health-Tech company. Our mission is to disrupt the expensive and inefficient Pharmacy Benefit Management (PBM) sector by building a next-generation drug acquisition platform driven by cutting edge technology, innovative cost saving tools, and best-in-class customer service. With hundreds of thousands of members onboarded since 2016, SmithRx has a solution that is resonating with clients all across the country.

We pride ourselves for our mission-driven and collaborative culture that inspires our employees to do their best work. We believe that the U.S healthcare system is in need of transformation, and we come to work each day dedicated to making that change a reality. At our core, we are guided by our company values of:
• Integrity: Do the right thing. Especially when it's hard.
• Courage: Embrace the challenge.
• Together: Build bridges and lift up your colleagues.

With fast-paced growth comes a multitude of data-related opportunities to explore and challenges to navigate. SmithRx's Data Analytics team is at the forefront of wrangling vast amounts of data, unlocking their complexities, and harnessing their insights to generate value for present and prospective clients. We seek a Data Analytics Lead to assist us in these exciting endeavors.

The Data Analytics Lead will operate as a part of SmithRx's growing Data Analytics team and report to the Senior Manager, Data Analytics. You will function as a generalist to start, functioning as a liaison between the data team and our stakeholder teams, which we organize under three broad verticals: Commercial Strategy, Operational Efficiency, and Customer Satisfaction. You will manage the data team's day-to-day relationship with these stakeholder teams and ensure we are providing them with the resources they need to operate effectively. As the Data Analytics Lead evolves in their role, you will assume greater oversight of one of these verticals.

The Data Analytics Lead will support junior team members in diving deep into our data, hunting for the business insights that will support key business needs and communicating them to decision-makers. Furthermore, you will guide the team in exploring the intricacies of our data – searching for patterns and discovering trends that will inform our business understanding and contribute to organizational strategy for years to come. Finally, you will lead the way in designing creative metrics and appealing visualizations for reporting that effectively communicate our value proposition and enhance the SmithRx product.

Our goal is for the Data Analytics Lead to leverage their analytical rigor, business acumen, and prior experience to showcase the robust, meaningful, and cost-effective product offering we provide for our clients and members.

What will you do:
• Lead the charge on partnering closely with our stakeholder teams to ensure all near and long term needs are scoped, documented, and have a place on the Data Analytics team's product roadmap
• Provide thought leadership for best practices and shape the team's approach to data cleaning, governance, analysis, visualization, and dissemination
• Guide team members in conducting rigorous, insightful analysis to not only answer the "what and when" questions, but also the "hows and whys"
• Create visual snapshots that tell clear, compelling stories and illustrate how SmithRx's value proposition makes a real-world impact for customers
• Manage ad hoc tickets via the team's helpdesk system, ensuring all tasks are assigned appropriately and have a clear timeline to completion
• Provide end-to-end mentorship to the team, shaping both day-to-day operations and also the 3-5 year vision for the Data Analytics team

What will you bring to SmithRx:
• 7-10 years of work experience massaging, interrogating, drawing insights from, visualizing, and presenting data required
• Healthcare and/or pharmacy experience preferred
• Bachelor's degree required / advanced degree preferred
• Advanced skill in SQL required
• Advanced skill in Tableau, Looker, Qlik, or similar data visualization software required
• Looker experience preferred
• Familiarity with additional data analysis tools (Python, R, Java, etc.) preferred

• Familiarity with Jira or similar project management tools required

• Self-starter mentality: ability to make informed decisions, find creative approaches to difficult challenges, and deliver on commitments

• Flexible, adaptable, and able to respond under the pressure of a fast-paced technology company

Responsibilities

Responsibilities

The RISQ Division's mission is to contribute to the sustainable and predictable growth of the SG Group by overseeing and independently challenging the objectives and strategies of the Business Lines. RISQ’s mission is to independently analyze, challenge, opine and monitor on the risk-taking activities of the Business Lines in order to get to the best possible outcome for the Bank. The RISQ division in the US supports all the activities in the Americas Region (US, Canada and Latin America), which is almost exclusively SGCIB-oriented.

Within the RISQ Division, the Operational Risk (“RISQ/AME/OPE”) department has the primary responsibility as the Second Line of Defense (“2LOD”) for developing, enforcing and overseeing the Operational Risk Framework based on SG Group, Regulator and peer best practices. The mission is to manage the operational risks and permanent control frameworks to which SG’s Americas operations (SG AMER) are exposed.

Key principles include:
• Clarifying the roles and accountabilities for Operational Risk specific programs cascaded from the US Exco Management to the First Line of Defense (“1LOD”), individual employees and Risk Management teams
• Ensuring regulatory requirements are met while providing maximum business value and efficiency
• Establishing and providing independent operational risk oversight of 1LOD owned operational risk responsibilities
• Providing guidance and advice to the lines of business on a day-to-day basis to pre-emptively identify, manage and mitigate operational risk throughout SG AMER
• Evaluating and escalating critical and emerging risks across the firm and to the Group level organization, and ensure proper controls are implemented
• Aggregating risks and information across SG AMER; ensuring escalation of non-compliance of risk limits and standards through SG AMER governance and reporting structure

Monitoring, Control & Reporting (MCR) team within RISQ/AME/OPE ensures that the processes and governance around operational risk (i.e. Operational Risk Event Collection/Reporting, Risk and Control Self-Assessment, etc.) respect the group policies and norms. MCR consolidates, analyses and escalates the operational risk reported by the various lines of defines to provide management with an executive view of the risk through governing committees or day to day interaction.
• Define and oversee the data collection process for the operational risk framework
• Produce operational risk indicators and analyse the data to find key insights
• Perform analysis to assess quality and meaning of data
• Preparing reports for the management stating trends, patterns and predictions using Operational Risk data
• Maintain and develop the Operational Risk framework
• Provide Support for OPE Analytics/Datalab project initiatives

During your VIE mission you will be in charge of these responsibilities :
• Produce operational risks reports, operational risk appetite statement metrics and key risk indicators for SG Americas to Senior Management
• Using statistical tools to Identify, analyse and interpret patterns and trends in complex data sets that could be helpful for diagnosis and prediction purposes
• Locate and define new process improvement opportunities and propose solutions to improve reporting efficiency
• Maintain the data source extracts to assist RISQ management in the monitoring and escalation of material operational risk incidents
• Participate/coordinate in projects particularly focused on the automation enhancements and documentation for operational risk management reporting and metric production
• Follow-up with business lines and support functions on areas of concern related to the Operational Risk Management Framework (i.e. operational risk events, metrics, action plans, etc.)

Job Purpose

The Data Analyst will act as a general consultant to the business regarding business intelligence (BI), analytics initiatives, designing, implementing and maintaining end-to-end solutions through the use of well-established and leading edge BI and analytics tools and techniques.

This role is responsible for collaborating with the business, defining business requirements, determining the appropriate solution to address the business problem at hand, and executing and deploying the solution in collaboration with various stakeholders as needed.

Additionally, the ability to support in the development and maintenance of sophisticated business intelligence infrastructure and databases is a key deliverable for this role.

The ideal candidate will possess acute analytical abilities, demonstrated experience with statistical analytics, strength in data visualization, along with excellent collaboration and communication skills. Consultant experience is a must.

Duties and responsibilities
• Act as a technical and strategic partner to internal clients across the organization, defining requirements and identifying the appropriate research approach/design to address business needs.
• Help lead staff through the adoption and utilization of analytics in their day-to-day decision-making ensuring analytics drive opportunity identification and appropriate investments.
• Consult on and deploy analytics solutions in collaboration with other areas of the division as needed.
• Extract and manipulate data from various sources and perform data analytics using suitable techniques to uncover insights that guide and inform relevant business decisions.
• Support in the design, development, and maintenance of visually appealing, intuitive, and functional Business Intelligence outputs (reports, dashboards, smart alerts, etc.) to enable all levels of the organization to constantly be aware of performance and effortlessly understand what is impacting it.
• Develop clear, concise, and comprehensive presentations of analytics results that emphasize actionable recommendations and insights to support the development of new strategies and tactics.
• Work to solution existing data, reporting and analytics inefficiencies ensuring identified solutions are consistent and scalable.

Qualifications
• A university degree in analytics, mathematics, statistics, business or related field.
• A minimum of 5 years of relevant analytics, insights, or BI experience.
• Strong understanding of data management concepts to effectively integrate and analyze data; ability to engage in meta-analysis, statistical analysis, big data, predictive modeling, and forecasting.
• Experience with Business Intelligence, data manipulation, and data science tools and their application (Cognos BI, Power BI, SiSense, SQL, Python, and/or similar tools).
• Proven ability to think strategically and to come up with solutions to loosely defined business problems.
• Strong interpersonal, collaboration, and problem-solving skills; a strong team player and collaborative with other departments.
• Experience working in an Agile environment is advantageous.

Job Description:

The Client Experience Office (CXO) is an important pillar of Sun Life's corporate strategy and as such, is seeking an experienced Senior Data Analyst to join our CXO Analytics team. This team is dedicated to supporting client growth and performance through extracting meaningful insights from enterprise data.

Reporting to the AVP, CXO Analytics, the Senior Data Analyst will play an integral role in migrating our existing Lead Program reporting from SAS to AWS through migrating the technology to our newest data stack and updating existing reporting to provide more insight, a robust data foundation, and easier to understand visuals. This is an exciting opportunity to build new reports using new data sources and new technology. Please note this is a 6-month contract opportunity.

What will you do?
• Design and engineer data products in Tableau
• Ensure that a high level of data quality and data integrity are maintained across all data sources
• Convert complex business and technical rules into logic for data flows, data pipelines and dashboards
• Develop visualization solutions that present data accurately and drive insights to guide business decisions and outcomes
• Collaborate with business stakeholders to understand reporting needs
• Work with our Data Enablement teams to implement data products for reporting needs
• Perform ad-hoc analysis to help explore new data questions

What do you need to succeed?
• 3-5 years of hands-on experience working with AWS technologies for data processing and analytics; demonstrated experience with relational database systems, relational models, and dimensional models
• 3-5 years of experience with engineering data products as input to various analytical models
• 3 years of experience in SQL with a proven track record in leveraging SQL and SQL-based programming to solve business problems
• 2 years of experience with AWS Glue for ETL
• Experience in building dashboards in Tableau or an equivalent tool, with the ability to produce well-designed interactive dashboards and automated reports
• Proven experience working with complex data sources and various data types to develop robust data foundations and production-grade data products
• Ability to translate complex business requirements into a set of data ingestion pseudocode

What would be nice to have?
• Experience with Salesforce
• Experience with SAS programming
• Experience working in a large financial services organization
• Knowledge of fundamental statistical models & techniques

What are the unique requirements?
• The candidate selected for this role is required to attain Canadian Reliability Security Clearance (administered by submitting fingerprints to the RCMP, who then conduct minimum 5-year history checks)
• To see if you are eligible for this clearance, please review the section 201 on the Federal Government site )

What's in it for you?
• Great Place to Work Certified in Canada and the US - 2022
• Great Place to Work award for Best Workplaces for #HybridWork - 2022
• Named "Best Places to Work" by Glassdoor - 2021
• Canada Award for Excellence for Mental Health at Work - 2021
• Flex hours and Flexible hybrid work model including in-country work-from-home if you prefer. #LI-Hybrid, #LI-Remote
• Be part of our continuous improvement journey in developing the next greatest digital enterprise experience.
• Work and professional development that is united by our Purpose: to help Clients and Employees achieve lifetime financial security and live healthier lives

Job Summary

UBC Sauder School of Business is one of the world's leading business faculties. The school consistently ranks among the top 100 in the world and is recognized internationally for excellence in research and learning, an outstanding faculty and unmatched global partnerships. A collaborative and respectful culture within which all members of our community can thrive is a key principle in our strategic plan, and one that underpins our educational mission.

We acknowledge that UBC Sauder at the Vancouver Campus is situated within the traditional, ancestral and unceded territory of the Musqueam. We acknowledge that UBC Sauder at the UBC Robson Square is situated on the traditional territory of the Musqueam, Squamish and Tsleil-Waututh.

The Creative Destruction Lab (CDL) is a nonprofit organization that delivers an objectives-based program for massively scalable, seed-stage, science- and technology-based companies with locations in Canada, USA, France and the UK. CDL-Vancouver is anchored at the UBC Sauder School of Business, supporting and contributing to the entire west coast innovation ecosystem in Canada and in the US.CDL-Vancouver works directly with start-up companies within the Climate, Compute, Biomedical Engineering, and Advanced Therapies ( ). .

CDL is a high priority and high-profile initiative for the UBC Sauder School of Business and UBC. Program outcomes can be expected to have a significant impact on UBC Sauder and UBC's public profile and standing in the eyes of Universities, the startup & technology sector, and the general public in both Canada and the US.

The Data Analyst works to maintain and transform data into meaningful insights regarding stakeholder behavior, trends, and operational effectiveness and develops new reporting tools and data

visualizations and representations to advise CDL senior leadership and support data-driven decision-making.

The Data Analyst works extensively with Saleforce, Airtable and Google Drive and manages the data flow and interaction between these platforms. As the data management expert, the Data Analyst facilitates informed decisions on strategic action items and advances CDL-Vancouver priorities by performing qualitative and quantitative research, designing reporting systems, overseeing data collection and conducting analyses. The incumbent designs, develops and implements methods associated to this research.

Organizational Status
Reports to CDL's Senior Project Manager. Works closely with the CDL Leadership team, Operations team, Partnerships team, and Venture Management team.

Work Performed
• Collects, analyzes, interprets and extracts data. Works with complex datasets to research, analyze and prepare statistical reports on key findings.
• Advises CDL leadership team, uses statistical analysis to evaluate progress towards strategic targets.
• Creates regular reports on key performance indicators (KPIs) on a regular basis to track progress and success.
• Conducts benchmarking research exercises and analysis to support CDL's objectives.
• Reorganizes and streamlines current databases to accurately synthesize reports, summaries, and dashboards to produce insights. Develops reporting schedule and creates and runs reports required for all levels of reporting.
• Maintains data and develops data quality assessments on main databases to ensure its accuracy and suitability.
• Recommends, develops, and implements process improvements to ensure the timely and accurate transfer of information into the CDL network-wide databases.
• In consultation with the team, builds solutions to simplify CDL's data infrastructure and data visualization tools to empower the team to access and leverage data independently.
• Builds automations to reduce manual work while increasing efficiency and accuracy.
• Manages key data collection and implements new processes to acquire and analyze information that has been identified as significant to the operation of the organization.
• Contributes to the identification of CDL's data needs and priorities for upgrades.
• Educates the larger team on how to use the tools according to the improved processes (on an ongoing basis). Provides training and answers questions around data management from CDL employees.
• Obtains and discloses confidential and sensitive information as appropriate, determining appropriate course of action, resolving details of unusual situations in the absence of established guidelines.
• Provides technical documentation of all aspects of the data management process.
• Performs other related duties.

Consequence of Error/Judgement

Responsible for providing accurate, potentially sensitive, and confidential information to other members of the team. Must respect the confidentiality of information handled.

Failure to exercise appropriate judgment could put the department in violation of privacy laws, increase direct costs, contribute to lost opportunities, damage the reputation of the university, and potentially negatively impact relationships and philanthropic support.

Supervision Received
Reports to CDL's Senior Project Manager. Also takes direction from CDL's Leadership team.

Supervision Given
None

Minimum Qualifications
Undergraduate degree in a relevant discipline. Minimum of two years of related experience, or the equivalent combination of education and experience.

- Willingness to respect diverse perspectives, including perspectives in conflict with one's own

Demonstrates a commitment to enhancing one's own awareness, knowledge, and skills related to equity, diversity, and inclusion

Preferred Qualifications
• A high degree of computer literacy and extensive experience with Microsoft 365 and Google Drive, in particular, demonstrated high-level proficiency with advanced Excel/Google Sheets functions (VLOOKUP, PivotTables, PowerPivot, etc.).
• Proficiency with statistics, data cleaning, data mapping, data manipulation, and reporting.
• Experience working with databases and CRMs, preferably Salesforce and Airtable.
• Willing to learn the existing processes in place in order to propose improvements.
• Intermediate coding skills to create solutions in Airtable Scripting Extension or alternative new solutions as the team's needs evolve. (Candidates with basic knowledge but a strong desire to develop coding skills will be considered.)
• Knowledge of Airtable Interfaces, Salesforce Dashboards, or any other data visualization software is strongly preferred.
• Strong strategic thinking, analytical, and decision-making skills.
• Ability to be thorough, accurate, and have a high level of attention to detail.
• Technical documentation skills.
• The ability to work as part of an integrated team in a fast-paced environment.
• Excellent communication (oral and written), interpersonal, organizational, and time management skills.
• Proactive, with demonstrated initiative and creative problem-solving skills.
• Understanding of privacy, copyright, and data security best practices.
• Proven quantitative research and analytical techniques with the ability to gather, evaluate and synthesize complex and large sets of data.
